51MachineType MachineTypeFor(maglev::ValueRepresentation repr) {
52 switch (repr) {
53 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
54 return MachineType::AnyTagged();
55 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
56 return MachineType::Int32();
57 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
58 return MachineType::Uint32();
59 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
60 return MachineType::IntPtr();
61 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
62 return MachineType::Float64();
63 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
64 // TODO(dmercadier): is this correct?
65 return MachineType::Float64();
66 }
67}

108 void PreProcessGraph(maglev::Graph* graph) {
109 for (maglev::BasicBlock* block : *graph) {
110 block_mapping_[block] =
111 block->is_loop() ? __ NewLoopHeader() : __ NewBlock();
112 }
113 // Constants are not in a block in Maglev but are in Turboshaft. We bind a
114 // block now, so that Constants can then be emitted.
115 __ Bind(__ NewBlock());
116
117 if (maglev_compilation_unit_->bytecode()
118 .incoming_new_target_or_generator_register()
119 .is_valid()) {
120 // The Maglev graph might contain a RegisterInput for
121 // kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister later in the graph, which in
122 // Turboshaft is represented as a Parameter. We create this Parameter
123 // here, because the Instruction Selector tends to be unhappy when
124 // Parameters are defined late in the graph.
125 int new_target_index = Linkage::GetJSCallNewTargetParamIndex(
126 maglev_compilation_unit_->parameter_count());
127 new_target_param_ = __ Parameter(
128 new_target_index, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), "%new.target");
129 }
130
131 // Maglev nodes often don't have the NativeContext as input, but instead
132 // rely on the MaglevAssembler to provide it during code generation, unlike
133 // Turboshaft nodes, which need the NativeContext as an explicit input if
134 // they use it. We thus emit a single NativeContext constant here, which we
135 // reuse later to construct Turboshaft nodes.
136 native_context_ =
137 __ HeapConstant(broker_->target_native_context().object());
138 }
139
140 void PostProcessGraph(maglev::Graph* graph) {}
141
142 void PreProcessBasicBlock(maglev::BasicBlock* block) {
143 if (__ current_block() != nullptr) {
144 // The first block for Constants doesn't end with a Jump, so we add one
145 // now.
146 __ Goto(Map(block));
147 }
148
149#ifdef DEBUG
150 loop_phis_first_input_.clear();
151 loop_phis_first_input_index_ = -1;
152 catch_block_begin_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
153#endif
154
155 if (block->is_loop() &&
156 MapContains(loop_single_edge_predecessors_, block)) {
157 EmitLoopSinglePredecessorBlock(block);
158 }
159
160 __ Bind(Map(block));
161
162 if (block->is_loop()) {
163 // The "permutation" stuff that comes afterwards in this function doesn't
164 // apply to loops, since loops always have 2 predecessors in Turboshaft,
165 // and in both Turboshaft and Maglev, the backedge is always the last
166 // predecessors, so we never need to reorder phi inputs.
167 return;
168 } else if (block->is_exception_handler_block()) {
169 // We need to emit the CatchBlockBegin at the begining of this block. Note
170 // that if this block has multiple predecessors (because multiple throwing
171 // operations are caught by the same catch handler), then edge splitting
172 // will have already created CatchBlockBegin operations in the
173 // predecessors, and calling `__ CatchBlockBegin` now will actually only
174 // emit a Phi of the CatchBlockBegin of the predecessors (which is exactly
175 // what we want). See the comment above CatchBlockBegin in
176 // TurboshaftAssemblerOpInterface.
177 catch_block_begin_ = __ CatchBlockBegin();
178 }
179
180 // Because of edge splitting in Maglev (which happens on Bind rather than on
181 // Goto), predecessors in the Maglev graph are not always ordered by their
182 // position in the graph (ie, block 4 could be the second predecessor and
183 // block 5 the first one). However, since we're processing the graph "in
184 // order" (because that's how the maglev GraphProcessor works), predecessors
185 // in the Turboshaft graph will be ordered by their position in the graph.
186 // We thus compute in {predecessor_permutation_} the Turboshaft predecessors
187 // position of each Maglev predecessor, and we'll use this later when
188 // emitting Phis to reorder their inputs.
189 predecessor_permutation_.clear();
190 if (block->has_phi()) {
191 for (int i = 0; i < block->predecessor_count(); ++i) {
192 Block* pred = Map(block->predecessor_at(i));
193 int pred_index = __ current_block() -> GetPredecessorIndex(pred);
194 DCHECK_IMPLIES(pred_index == -1,
195 block->is_loop() && i == block->predecessor_count() - 1);
196 predecessor_permutation_.push_back(pred_index);
197 }
198 }
199 }
200
201 void EmitLoopSinglePredecessorBlock(maglev::BasicBlock* block) {
202 DCHECK(block->is_loop());
203 DCHECK(MapContains(loop_single_edge_predecessors_, block));
204 Block* loop_pred = loop_single_edge_predecessors_[block];
205 __ Bind(loop_pred);
206
207 // Now we need to emit Phis (one per loop phi in {block}, which should
208 // contain the same input except for the backedge).
209 loop_phis_first_input_.clear();
210 loop_phis_first_input_index_ = 0;
211 for (maglev::Phi* phi : *block->phis()) {
212 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> inputs;
213 constexpr int kSkipBackedge = 1;
214 for (int i = 0; i < phi->input_count() - kSkipBackedge; i++) {
215 inputs.push_back(Map(phi->input(i)));
216 }
217 loop_phis_first_input_.push_back(
218 __ Phi(base::VectorOf(inputs),
219 RegisterRepresentationFor(phi->value_representation())));
220 }
221
222 // Actually jumping to the loop.
223 __ Goto(Map(block));
224 }

268 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::InitialValue* node,
269 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
270 // TODO(dmercadier): InitialValues are much simpler in Maglev because they
271 // are mapped directly to interpreter registers, whereas Turbofan changes
272 // the indices, making everything more complex. We should try to have the
273 // same InitialValues in Turboshaft as in Maglev, in order to simplify
274 // things.
275#ifdef DEBUG
276 char* debug_name = strdup(node->source().ToString().c_str());
277#else
278 char* debug_name = nullptr;
279#endif
280 interpreter::Register source = node->source();
281 V<Object> value;
282 if (source.is_function_closure()) {
283 // The function closure is a Parameter rather than an OsrValue even when
284 // OSR-compiling.
285 value = __ Parameter(Linkage::kJSCallClosureParamIndex,
286 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), debug_name);
287 } else if (maglev_compilation_unit_->is_osr()) {
288 int index;
289 if (source.is_current_context()) {
290 index = Linkage::kOsrContextSpillSlotIndex;
291 } else if (source == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
292 index = Linkage::kOsrAccumulatorRegisterIndex;
293 } else if (source.is_parameter()) {
294 index = source.ToParameterIndex();
295 } else {
296 // For registers, recreate the index computed by FillWithOsrValues in
297 // BytecodeGraphBuilder.
298 index = source.index() + InterpreterFrameConstants::kExtraSlotCount +
299 maglev_compilation_unit_->parameter_count();
300 }
301 value = __ OsrValue(index);
302 } else {
303 int index = source.ToParameterIndex();
304 if (source.is_current_context()) {
305 index = Linkage::GetJSCallContextParamIndex(
306 maglev_compilation_unit_->parameter_count());
307 } else {
308 index = source.ToParameterIndex();
309 }
310 value = __ Parameter(index, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), debug_name);
311 }
312 SetMap(node, value);
313 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
314 }

332 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Phi* node,
333 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
334 int input_count = node->input_count();
335 RegisterRepresentation rep =
336 RegisterRepresentationFor(node->value_representation());
337 if (node->is_exception_phi()) {
338 if (node->owner() == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
339 DCHECK(catch_block_begin_.valid());
340 SetMap(node, catch_block_begin_);
341 } else {
342 SetMap(node, __ GetVariable(regs_to_vars_[node->owner().index()]));
343 }
344 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
345 }
346 if (__ current_block()->IsLoop()) {
347 DCHECK(state.block()->is_loop());
348 OpIndex first_phi_input;
349 if (state.block()->predecessor_count() > 2) {
350 // This loop has multiple forward edge in Maglev, so we should have
351 // created an intermediate block in Turboshaft, which will be the only
352 // predecessor of the Turboshaft loop, and from which we'll find the
353 // first input for this loop phi.
354 DCHECK_EQ(loop_phis_first_input_.size(),
355 static_cast<size_t>(state.block()->phis()->LengthForTest()));
356 DCHECK_GE(loop_phis_first_input_index_, 0);
357 DCHECK_LT(loop_phis_first_input_index_, loop_phis_first_input_.size());
358 DCHECK(MapContains(loop_single_edge_predecessors_, state.block()));
359 DCHECK_EQ(loop_single_edge_predecessors_[state.block()],
360 __ current_block()->LastPredecessor());
361 first_phi_input = loop_phis_first_input_[loop_phis_first_input_index_];
362 loop_phis_first_input_index_++;
363 } else {
364 DCHECK_EQ(input_count, 2);
365 DCHECK_EQ(state.block()->predecessor_count(), 2);
366 DCHECK(loop_phis_first_input_.empty());
367 first_phi_input = Map(node->input(0));
368 }
369 SetMap(node, __ PendingLoopPhi(first_phi_input, rep));
370 } else {
371 DCHECK(!predecessor_permutation_.empty());
372 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> inputs;
373 for (int i = 0; i < input_count; ++i) {
374 inputs.push_back(Map(node->input(predecessor_permutation_[i])));
375 }
376 SetMap(node, __ Phi(base::VectorOf(inputs), rep));
377 }
378 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
379 }

381 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Call* node,
382 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
383 V<FrameState> frame_state = BuildFrameState(node->lazy_deopt_info());
384 V<Object> function = Map(node->function());
385 V<Context> context = Map(node->context());
386
387 Builtin builtin;
388 switch (node->target_type()) {
389 case maglev::Call::TargetType::kAny:
390 switch (node->receiver_mode()) {
391 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
392 builtin = Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsNullOrUndefined;
393 break;
394 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
395 builtin = Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsNotNullOrUndefined;
396 break;
397 case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny:
398 builtin = Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsAny;
399 break;
400 }
401 break;
402 case maglev::Call::TargetType::kJSFunction:
403 switch (node->receiver_mode()) {
404 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
405 builtin = Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsNullOrUndefined;
406 break;
407 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
408 builtin = Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsNotNullOrUndefined;
409 break;
410 case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny:
411 builtin = Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsAny;
412 break;
413 }
414 break;
415 }
416
417 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
418 arguments.push_back(function);
419 arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args()));
420 for (auto arg : node->args()) {
421 arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
422 }
423 arguments.push_back(context);
424
425 SetMap(node,
426 GenerateBuiltinCall(node, builtin, frame_state,
427 base::VectorOf(arguments), node->num_args()));
428
429 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
430 }
431 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallKnownJSFunction* node,
432 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
433 ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
434
435 V<FrameState> frame_state = BuildFrameState(node->lazy_deopt_info());
436 V<Object> callee = Map(node->closure());
437 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
438 arguments.push_back(Map(node->receiver()));
439 for (int i = 0; i < node->num_args(); i++) {
440 arguments.push_back(Map(node->arg(i)));
441 }
442
443 arguments.push_back(Map(node->new_target()));
444 arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(JSParameterCount(node->num_args())));
445
446 // Load the context from {callee}.
447 OpIndex context =
448 __ LoadField(callee, AccessBuilder::ForJSFunctionContext());
449 arguments.push_back(context);
450
451 const CallDescriptor* descriptor = Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
452 graph_zone(), false, 1 + node->num_args(),
453 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState | CallDescriptor::kCanUseRoots);
454 SetMap(node, __ Call(V<CallTarget>::Cast(callee), frame_state,
455 base::VectorOf(arguments),
456 TSCallDescriptor::Create(descriptor, CanThrow::kYes,
457 graph_zone())));
458
459 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
460 }
461 V<Any> GenerateBuiltinCall(
462 maglev::NodeBase* node, Builtin builtin, V<FrameState> frame_state,
463 base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
464 base::Optional<int> stack_arg_count = base::nullopt) {
465 ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
466
467 Callable callable =
468 Builtins::CallableFor(isolate_->GetMainThreadIsolateUnsafe(), builtin);
469 const CallInterfaceDescriptor& descriptor = callable.descriptor();
470 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
471 graph_zone(), descriptor,
472 stack_arg_count.has_value() ? stack_arg_count.value()
473 : descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(),
474 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
475 V<Code> stub_code = __ HeapConstant(callable.code());
476
477 return __ Call(stub_code, frame_state, base::VectorOf(arguments),
478 TSCallDescriptor::Create(call_descriptor, CanThrow::kYes,
479 graph_zone()));
480 }
481 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallBuiltin* node,
482 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
483 V<FrameState> frame_state = BuildFrameState(node->lazy_deopt_info());
484
485 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
486 for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCountWithoutContext(); i++) {
487 arguments.push_back(Map(node->input(i)));
488 }
489
490 if (node->has_feedback()) {
491 arguments.push_back(__ TaggedIndexConstant(node->feedback().index()));
492 arguments.push_back(__ HeapConstant(node->feedback().vector));
493 }
494
495 if (Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(node->builtin())
496 .HasContextParameter()) {
497 arguments.push_back(Map(node->context_input()));
498 }
499
500 SetMap(node, GenerateBuiltinCall(node, node->builtin(), frame_state,
501 base::VectorOf(arguments)));
502
503 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
504 }
505 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallRuntime* node,
506 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
507 ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
508
509 auto c_entry_stub = __ CEntryStubConstant(
510 isolate_->GetMainThreadIsolateUnsafe(), node->ReturnCount());
511
512 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
513 graph_zone(), node->function_id(), node->num_args(),
514 Operator::kNoProperties, CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
515
516 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
517 for (int i = 0; i < node->num_args(); i++) {
518 arguments.push_back(Map(node->arg(i)));
519 }
520
521 arguments.push_back(
522 __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(node->function_id())));
523 arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args()));
524
525 arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
526
527 OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state = OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
528 if (call_descriptor->NeedsFrameState()) {
529 frame_state = BuildFrameState(node->lazy_deopt_info());
530 }
531
532 SetMap(node, __ Call(c_entry_stub, frame_state, base::VectorOf(arguments),
533 TSCallDescriptor::Create(
534 call_descriptor, CanThrow::kYes, graph_zone())));
535
536 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
537 }

689 arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));

691 SetMap(node, __ Call(stub_code, frame_state, base::VectorOf(arguments),
692 TSCallDescriptor::Create(
693 call_descriptor, CanThrow::kYes, graph_zone())));

695 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

792 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckMaps* node,
793 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
794 Label<> done(this);
795 V<FrameState> frame_state = BuildFrameState(node->eager_deopt_info());
796 if (node->check_type() == maglev::CheckType::kCheckHeapObject) {
797 OpIndex is_smi = __ IsSmi(Map(node->receiver_input()));
798 if (AnyMapIsHeapNumber(node->maps())) {
799 // Smis count as matching the HeapNumber map, so we're done.
800 GOTO_IF(is_smi, done);
801 } else {
802 __ DeoptimizeIf(is_smi, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap,
803 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
804 }
805 }
806 __ CheckMaps(Map(node->receiver_input()), frame_state, node->maps(),
807 CheckMapsFlag::kNone,
808 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
809
810 if (done.has_incoming_jump()) {
811 GOTO(done);
812 BIND(done);
813 }
814 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
815 }

1276 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckJSDataViewBounds* node,
1277 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1278 V<FrameState> frame_state = BuildFrameState(node->eager_deopt_info());
1279 // Normal DataView (backed by AB / SAB) or non-length tracking backed by
1280 // GSAB.
1281 V<WordPtr> byte_length =
1282 __ LoadField<WordPtr>(Map<JSTypedArray>(node->receiver_input()),
1283 AccessBuilder::ForJSDataViewByteLength());
1284
1285 int element_size = ExternalArrayElementSize(node->element_type());
1286 if (element_size > 1) {
1287 // For element_size larger than 1, we need to make sure that {index} is
1288 // less than {byte_length}, but also that {index+element_size} is less
1289 // than {byte_length}. We do this by subtracting {element_size-1} from
1290 // {byte_length}: if the resulting length is greater than 0, then we can
1291 // just treat {element_size} as 1 and check if {index} is less than this
1292 // new {byte_length}.
1293 DCHECK(element_size == 2 || element_size == 4 || element_size == 8);
1294 byte_length = __ WordPtrSub(byte_length, element_size - 1);
1295 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ IntPtrLessThan(byte_length, 0), frame_state,
1296 DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds,
1297 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
1298 }
1299 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
1300 __ Uint32LessThan(Map<Word32>(node->index_input()),
1301 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(byte_length)),
1302 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds,
1303 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
1304 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1305 }

1361 void BuildJump(maglev::BasicBlock* target) {
1362 Block* destination = Map(target);
1363 if (target->is_loop() && target->predecessor_count() > 2) {
1364 // This loop has multiple forward edge in Maglev, so we'll create an extra
1365 // block in Turboshaft that will be the only predecessor.
1366 auto it = loop_single_edge_predecessors_.find(target);
1367 if (it != loop_single_edge_predecessors_.end()) {
1368 destination = it->second;
1369 } else {
1370 Block* loop_only_pred = __ NewBlock();
1371 loop_single_edge_predecessors_[target] = loop_only_pred;
1372 destination = loop_only_pred;
1373 }
1374 }
1375 __ Goto(destination);
1376 }

1379 BuildJump(node->target());
1380 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

1385 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

1433 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::TestTypeOf* node,
1434 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1435 V<Object> input = Map(node->value());
1436 V<Boolean> result;
1437 switch (node->literal()) {
1438 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kNumber:
1439 result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
1440 __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNumber,
1441 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
1442 break;
1443 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kString:
1444 result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
1445 __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kString,
1446 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));

1449 result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
1450 __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSymbol,
1451 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
1452 break;
1453 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kBigInt:
1454 result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
1455 __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt,
1456 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
1457 break;
1458 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kFunction:
1459 result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
1460 __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kDetectableCallable,
1461 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
1462 break;
1463 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kBoolean:
1464 result = __ Select(__ RootEqual(input, RootIndex::kTrueValue, isolate_),
1465 __ HeapConstant(factory_->true_value()),
1466 __ HeapConstant(factory_->false_value()),
1467 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
1468 SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
1469 break;
1470 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kUndefined:
1471 result = __ Select(__ RootEqual(input, RootIndex::kNullValue, isolate_),
1472 __ HeapConstant(factory_->false_value()),
1473 ConvertWord32ToJSBool(__ ObjectIs(
1474 input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kUndetectable,
1475 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone)),
1476 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
1477 SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
1478 break;
1479 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kObject:
1480 result = __ Select(__ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNonCallable,
1481 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone),
1482 __ HeapConstant(factory_->true_value()),
1483 __ RootEqual(input, RootIndex::kNullValue, isolate_),
1484 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
1485 SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
1486 break;
1487 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kOther:
1488 UNREACHABLE(); // Should never be emitted.
1489 }

1491 SetMap(node, result);
1492 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1493 }

1590 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Switch* node,
1591 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1592 compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case* cases =
1593 __ output_graph().graph_zone()
1594 -> AllocateArray<compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case>(
1595 node->size());
1596 int case_value_base = node->value_base();
1597 for (int i = 0; i < node->size(); i++) {
1598 cases[i] = {i + case_value_base, Map(node->targets()[i].block_ptr()),
1599 BranchHint::kNone};
1600 }
1601 Block* default_block;
1602 bool emit_default_block = false;
1603 if (node->has_fallthrough()) {
1604 default_block = Map(state.next_block());
1605 } else {
1606 default_block = __ NewBlock();
1607 emit_default_block = true;
1608 }
1609 __ Switch(Map(node->value()), base::VectorOf(cases, node->size()),
1610 default_block);
1611 if (emit_default_block) {
1612 __ Bind(default_block);
1613 __ Unreachable();
1614 }
1615 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1616 }

1763 __ Float64RoundUp(input));

1765 result = __ Float64Sub(result, 1.0);
1766 }

1769 }

1913 // means that they can be converted to Smis, and otherwise they should

1919 : ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kHeapNumber;

1927 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::HoleyFloat64ToTagged* node,
1928 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1929 Label<Object> done(this);
1930 V<Float64> input = Map(node->input());
1931 if (node->conversion_mode() ==
1932 maglev::HoleyFloat64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi) {
1933 // ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive cannot at the same time canonicalize smis
1934 // and handle holes. We thus manually insert a smi check when the
1935 // conversion_mode is CanonicalizeSmi.
1936 IF (__ Float64IsSmi(input)) {
1937 GOTO(done,
1938 __ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
1939 __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(input),
1940 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi,
1941 RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
1942 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned,
1943 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero));
1944 }
1945 }
1946 GOTO(done, __ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
1947 Map(node->input()),
1948 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
1949 kHeapNumberOrUndefined,
1950 RegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
1951 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned,
1952 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero));
1953 BIND(done, result);
1954 SetMap(node, result);
1955 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

2344
2345 V<FrameState> BuildFrameState(maglev::InterpretedDeoptFrame& frame,
2346 OutputFrameStateCombine combine,
2347 bool is_topmost) {
2348 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!is_topmost, combine.IsOutputIgnored());
2349 FrameStateData::Builder builder;
2350
2351 if (frame.parent() != nullptr) {
2352 V<FrameState> parent_frame = BuildParentFrameState(*frame.parent());
2353 builder.AddParentFrameState(parent_frame);
2354 }
2355
2356 // Closure
2357 AddDeoptInput(builder, frame.closure());
2358
2359 // Parameters
2360 frame.frame_state()->ForEachParameter(
2361 frame.unit(), [&](maglev::ValueNode* value, interpreter::Register reg) {
2362 AddDeoptInput(builder, value);
2363 });
2364
2365 // Context
2366 AddDeoptInput(builder, frame.frame_state()->context(frame.unit()));
2367
2368 // Locals
2369 // ForEachLocal in Maglev skips over dead registers, but we still need to
2370 // call AddUnusedRegister on the Turboshaft FrameStateData Builder.
2371 // {local_index} is used to keep track of such unused registers.
2372 // Among the variables not included in ForEachLocal is the Accumulator (but
2373 // this is fine since there is an entry in the state specifically for the
2374 // accumulator later).
2375 int local_index = 0;
2376 frame.frame_state()->ForEachLocal(
2377 frame.unit(), [&](maglev::ValueNode* value, interpreter::Register reg) {
2378 while (local_index < reg.index()) {
2379 builder.AddUnusedRegister();
2380 local_index++;
2381 }
2382 AddDeoptInput(builder, value);
2383 local_index++;
2384 });
2385 for (; local_index < frame.unit().register_count(); local_index++) {
2386 builder.AddUnusedRegister();
2387 }
2388
2389 // Accumulator
2390 // When `combine` is PokeAt(0), the value of the accumulator is produced by
2391 // the function that lazy deopts, and thus it shouldn't be in the
2392 // FrameState (since the FrameState is defined before the function is
2393 // called), so in that case we set the Accumulator to UnusedRegister, even
2394 // if it is alive.
2395 // TODO(dmercadier): the "combine != PokeAt(0)" is fine for now since we
2396 // don't have PokeAt with other values than 0 for now, but once we do, we
2397 // should use instead something similar to InReturnValues in Maglev.
2398 if (is_topmost && frame.frame_state()->liveness()->AccumulatorIsLive() &&
2399 combine != OutputFrameStateCombine::PokeAt(0)) {
2400 AddDeoptInput(builder, frame.frame_state()->accumulator(frame.unit()));
2401 } else {
2402 builder.AddUnusedRegister();
2403 }
2404
2405 const FrameStateInfo* frame_state_info = MakeFrameStateInfo(frame, combine);
2406 return __ FrameState(
2407 builder.Inputs(), builder.inlined(),
2408 builder.AllocateFrameStateData(*frame_state_info, graph_zone()));
2409 }

2460 enum class Sign { kSigned, kUnsigned };
2461 template <typename rep>
2462 V<Word32> ConvertCompare(maglev::Input left_input, maglev::Input right_input,
2463 ::Operation operation, Sign sign) {
2464 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
2465 (std::is_same_v<rep, Float64> || std::is_same_v<rep, Float32>),
2466 sign == Sign::kSigned);
2467 ComparisonOp::Kind kind;
2468 bool swap_inputs = false;
2469 switch (operation) {
2470 case ::Operation::kEqual:
2471 case ::Operation::kStrictEqual:
2472 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual;
2473 break;
2474 case ::Operation::kLessThan:
2475 kind = sign == Sign::kSigned ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan
2476 : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
2477 break;
2478 case ::Operation::kLessThanOrEqual:
2479 kind = sign == Sign::kSigned
2480 ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual
2481 : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
2482 break;
2483 case ::Operation::kGreaterThan:
2484 kind = sign == Sign::kSigned ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan
2485 : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
2486 swap_inputs = true;
2487 break;
2488 case ::Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual:
2489 kind = sign == Sign::kSigned
2490 ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual
2491 : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
2492 swap_inputs = true;
2493 break;
2494 default:
2495 UNREACHABLE();
2496 }
2497 V<rep> left = Map(left_input);
2498 V<rep> right = Map(right_input);
2499 if (swap_inputs) std::swap(left, right);
2500 return __ Comparison(left, right, kind, V<rep>::rep);
2501 }
2502
2503 V<Word32> ConvertInt32Compare(maglev::Input left_input,
2504 maglev::Input right_input,
2505 maglev::AssertCondition condition,
2506 bool* negate_result) {
2507 ComparisonOp::Kind kind;
2508 bool swap_inputs = false;
2509 switch (condition) {
2510 case maglev::AssertCondition::kEqual:
2511 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual;
2512 break;
2513 case maglev::AssertCondition::kNotEqual:
2514 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual;
2515 *negate_result = true;
2516 break;
2517 case maglev::AssertCondition::kLessThan:
2518 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan;
2519 break;
2520 case maglev::AssertCondition::kLessThanEqual:
2521 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual;
2522 break;
2523 case maglev::AssertCondition::kGreaterThan:
2524 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan;
2525 swap_inputs = true;
2526 break;
2527 case maglev::AssertCondition::kGreaterThanEqual:
2528 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual;
2529 swap_inputs = true;
2530 break;
2531 case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan:
2532 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
2533 break;
2534 case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
2535 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
2536 break;
2537 case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedGreaterThan:
2538 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
2539 swap_inputs = true;
2540 break;
2541 case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
2542 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
2543 swap_inputs = true;
2544 break;
2545 }
2546 V<Word32> left = Map(left_input);
2547 V<Word32> right = Map(right_input);
2548 if (swap_inputs) std::swap(left, right);
2549 return __ Comparison(left, right, kind, WordRepresentation::Word32());
2550 }

2628 class ThrowingScope {
2629 // In Maglev, exception handlers have no predecessors, and their Phis are a
2630 // bit special: they all correspond to interpreter registers, and get
2631 // eventually initialized with the value that their predecessors have for
2632 // the corresponding interpreter registers.
2633
2634 // In Turboshaft, exception handlers have predecessors and contain regular
2635 // phis. Creating a ThrowingScope takes care of recording in Variables
2636 // the current value of interpreter registers (right before emitting a node
2637 // that can throw), and sets the current_catch_block of the Assembler.
2638 // Throwing operations that are emitted while the scope is active will
2639 // automatically be wired to the catch handler. Then, when calling
2640 // Process(Phi) on exception phis (= when processing the catch handler),
2641 // these Phis will be mapped to the Variable corresponding to their owning
2642 // intepreter register.
2643
2644 public:
2645 ThrowingScope(GraphBuilder* builder, maglev::NodeBase* throwing_node)
2646 : builder_(*builder) {
2647 DCHECK(throwing_node->properties().can_throw());
2648 const maglev::ExceptionHandlerInfo* info =
2649 throwing_node->exception_handler_info();
2650 if (!info->HasExceptionHandler() || info->ShouldLazyDeopt()) return;
2651
2652 maglev::BasicBlock* block = info->catch_block.block_ptr();
2653 auto* liveness = block->state()->frame_state().liveness();
2654
2655 maglev::LazyDeoptInfo* deopt_info = throwing_node->lazy_deopt_info();
2656 const maglev::InterpretedDeoptFrame* lazy_frame;
2657 switch (deopt_info->top_frame().type()) {
2658 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame:
2659 lazy_frame = &deopt_info->top_frame().as_interpreted();
2660 break;
2661 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInlinedArgumentsFrame:
2662 UNREACHABLE();
2663 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame:
2664 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame:
2665 lazy_frame = &deopt_info->top_frame().parent()->as_interpreted();
2666 break;
2667 }
2668
2669 lazy_frame->frame_state()->ForEachValue(
2670 lazy_frame->unit(), [this, liveness](maglev::ValueNode* value,
2671 interpreter::Register reg) {
2672 if (!reg.is_parameter() && !liveness->RegisterIsLive(reg.index())) {
2673 // Skip, since not live at the handler offset.
2674 return;
2675 }
2676 auto it = builder_.regs_to_vars_.find(reg.index());
2677 Variable var;
2678 if (it == builder_.regs_to_vars_.end()) {
2679 var = __ NewVariable(RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
2680 builder_.regs_to_vars_.insert({reg.index(), var});
2681 } else {
2682 var = it->second;
2683 }
2684 __ SetVariable(var, builder_.Map(value));
2685 });
2686
2687 DCHECK_EQ(__ current_catch_block(), nullptr);
2688 __ set_current_catch_block(builder_.Map(block));
2689 }
2690
2691 ~ThrowingScope() {
2692 // Resetting the catch handler. It is always set on a case-by-case basis
2693 // before emitting a throwing node, so there is no need to "reset the
2694 // previous catch handler" or something like that, since there is no
2695 // previous handler (there is a DCHECK in the ThrowingScope constructor
2696 // checking that the current_catch_block is indeed nullptr when the scope
2697 // is created).
2698 __ set_current_catch_block(nullptr);
2699 }
2700
2701 private:
2702 GraphBuilder::AssemblerT& Asm() { return builder_.Asm(); }
2703 GraphBuilder& builder_;
2704 };

2740 // there is no such operation, and the exception is instead populated into the
2741 // accumulator by the throwing code, and is then loaded in Maglev through an
2742 // exception phi. When emitting a Turboshaft exception block, we thus store
2743 // the CatchBlockBegin in {catch_block_begin_}, which we then use when trying
2744 // to map the exception phi corresponding to the accumulator.

2748 // have a single one. When a Maglev loop has multiple forward edge, we create
2749 // an additional Turboshaft block before (which we record in
2750 // {loop_single_edge_predecessors_}), and jumps to the loop will instead go to
2751 // this additional block, which will become the only forward predecessor of
2752 // the loop.
2753 ZoneUnorderedMap<maglev::BasicBlock*, Block*> loop_single_edge_predecessors_;
2754 // When we create an additional loop predecessor for loops that have multiple
2755 // forward predecessors, we store the newly created phis in
2756 // {loop_phis_first_input_}, so that we can then use them as the first input
2757 // of the original loop phis. {loop_phis_first_input_index_} is used as an
2758 // index in {loop_phis_first_input_} in VisitPhi so that we know where to find
2759 // the first input for the current loop phi.
2760 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> loop_phis_first_input_;
2761 int loop_phis_first_input_index_ = -1;

2764 V<Object> new_target_param_ = OpIndex::Invalid();

2798void MaglevGraphBuildingPhase::Run(PipelineData* data, Zone* temp_zone) {
2799 JSHeapBroker* broker = data->broker();
2800 UnparkedScopeIfNeeded unparked_scope(broker);
2801
2802 auto compilation_info = maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo::New(
2803 data->isolate(), broker, data->info()->closure(),
2804 data->info()->osr_offset());
2805
2806 if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
2807 PrintBytecode(*data, compilation_info.get());
2808 }
2809
2810 LocalIsolate* local_isolate = broker->local_isolate()
2811 ? broker->local_isolate()
2812 : broker->isolate()->AsLocalIsolate();
2813 maglev::Graph* maglev_graph =
2814 maglev::Graph::New(temp_zone, data->info()->is_osr());
2815 if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
2816 compilation_info->set_graph_labeller(new maglev::MaglevGraphLabeller());
2817 }
2818 maglev::MaglevGraphBuilder maglev_graph_builder(
2819 local_isolate, compilation_info->toplevel_compilation_unit(),
2820 maglev_graph);
2821 maglev_graph_builder.Build();
2822
2823 // TODO(dmercadier, nicohartmann): remove the MaglevPhiRepresentationSelector
2824 // once we have representation selection / simplified lowering in Turboshaft.
2825 maglev::GraphProcessor<maglev::MaglevPhiRepresentationSelector>
2826 representation_selector(&maglev_graph_builder);
2827 representation_selector.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
2828
2829 if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
2830 PrintMaglevGraph(*data, compilation_info.get(), maglev_graph);
2831 }
2832
2833 maglev::GraphProcessor<GraphBuilder, true> builder(
2834 data, data->graph(), temp_zone,
2835 compilation_info->toplevel_compilation_unit());
2836 builder.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
2837}
